indian border regions during the summer monsoon season. respect[edit] the king and former king are accorded a great deal of respect in bhutan. it is wise to bear this in mind when conversing with local people. sacred objects. always pass mani stones, stupas and other religious objects with your right side nearest to the object, and turn prayer wheels in a clockwise direction. never sit on mani stones or stupas. clothing. when visiting temples, remove shoes and head gear and wear clothing that expresses respect for the sacred nature of the site. you will need to wear pants and long 